properties.headline: Dense Fog Advisory issued January 4 at 8:37AM EST until January 4 at 1:00PM EST by NWS Mount Holly NJ
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Gale Warning, northwest winds 20 to 30 kt with
gusts up to 40 kt and seas 4 to 7 feet expected. For the Dense
Fog Advisory, dense fog will reduce visibility to one mile or
less at times.

* WHERE...The Atlantic coastal waters adjacent to New Jersey.

* WHEN...For the Gale Warning, from midnight tonight to 1 PM EST
Sunday. For the Dense Fog Advisory, until 1 PM EST this
afternoon.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will cause hazardous seas which could
capsize or damage vessels. Low visibility will make navigation
difficult.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should alter plans to avoid these hazardous conditions.
Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for severe conditions.

If you must navigate, proceed with caution. Use proper fog
signals. Make sure all running lights are on. Remember to use
your radar and compass.

NWSheadline: DENSE FOG ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 1 PM EST THIS AFTERNOON... ...GALE WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM MIDNIGHT TONIGHT TO 1 PM EST SUNDAY
